---
<a name='hBasics'></a> 
>> Basics
*Base script*
To see a skeleton script for the fantomCX, have a look at the [[./data/fantomCX/examples/BaseScript/BaseScript.cxs|BaseScript.cxs]] script. 

---
<a name='hInput'></a>
>> Input
*Keymapping*
Sometimes you need to support different input schemes for your games. The [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Input/KeyMapping/KeyMapping.cxs|KeyMapping.cxs]] shows you how you can handle this. 

*Swipe/Gesture detection*
To find out how to use the swipe gesture detection, check out the [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Input/SwipeDetection/SwipeDetection.cxs|SwipeDetection.cxs]] script.

*Touch Input*
To check for touch input and maybe drag and drop an object, try this example [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Input/TouchInput/DragNDrop/DragNDrop.cxs|DragNDrop.cxs]].

*Extended touch Input*
If you need to check if a touch enters or exits an object, try this example [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Input/TouchInputEX/TouchInputEX.cxs|TouchInputEX.cxs]].

---
<a name='hLayer'></a>
>> Layer managment
*Scrolling layers*
If scrolling layers is still a black book for you, then maybe this script from fellow fantomCX user Douglas Williams will help you... [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Layer/ScrollingLayers/ScrollingLayers.cxs|ScrollingLayers.cxs]]

*Scaling layers*
When you need to scale a layer and set its scissor, look at this example: [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Layer/ScalingLayers/ScalingLayers.cxs|ScalingLayers.cxs]]

---
<a name='hLocalization'></a>
>> Localization
*Multiple languages*
If you need a simple way to display text in different languages then have a look at this script: [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Localization/Localization.cxs|Localization.cxs]]. 

---
<a name='hMisc'></a>
>> Misc
*Jump 'n' example*
There are several ways to create a jump 'n' run game in fantomCX. This script by Douglas Williams shows you one way: [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Misc/RunJump/RunJump.cxs|RunJump.cxs]]. 

*Multi class projects*
If you wonder how to split your project into several classes, have a look here: [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Misc/MultiClass/MultiClass.cxs|MultiClass.cxs]]. 

*Update objects*
To see how you can update your objects, have a look here: [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Misc/UpdateObjects/UpdateObjects.cxs|UpdateObjects.cxs]]. 

---
<a name='hObjects'></a>
>> Objects

>>> Appearence
*Set the blend mode*
Sometimes you need to see the blendmode of an object. For this you can study the [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Objects/Appearance/BlendMode/BlendMode.cxs|BlendMode.cxs]] script.

*Let an object flash*
If you need to draw attention to an object, let it flash like in this script (extended by Douglas Williams)... [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Objects/Appearance/FlashObject/FlashObject2.cxs|FlashObject2.cxs]] 

*9-Slice scaling*
Espercially for GUI elements which need nice scaliong without stretching to much 9-Slice (aka 9-Patch) scaling is the way to go. So look at this example: [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Objects/Appearance/9SliceScaling/9SliceScaling.cxs|9SliceScaling.cxs]] 

>>> Behaviour
*Object movement*
If you want to find out how to move objects and handle them in the OnObjectUpdate event, have a look at the [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Objects/Behaviour/ObjectMovement/ObjectMovement.cxs|ObjectMovement.cxs]] script. 

>>> Collision detection
*Collision checks between objects*
If you need to check for collisions between your objects, look at this example: [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Objects/Collision/Collision.cxs|Collision.cxs]]. 

>>> Object creation
*Animate an object*
Besides using an image strip like you do in Mojo, you can build animations in fantomCX by adding several images to an object. Have a look at this example: [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Objects/Creation/AnimObject/AnimObject.cxs|AnimObject.cxs]]. 

*Copy an object*
When you need to copy an object, have a look at the [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Objects/Creation/CopyObject/CopyObject.cxs|CopyObject.cxs]] script. 

*Drawing Primitives*
fantomCX supports different drawing primitves and the [[./data/fantomCX//examples/Objects/Creation/CreatePrimitives/CreatePrimitives.cxs|CreatePrimitives.cxs]] script by Douglas Williams tell you how. 

*Extend an object*
When you need to extend an object, have a look at the [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Objects/Creation/CustomObject/CustomObject.cxs|CustomObject.cxs]] script. 

*Load images*
When you need to load images, it is good to have a look at this example: [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Objects/Creation/LoadImage/LoadImage.cxs|LoadImage.cxs]]. 

*Object pooling*
If you need object pooling, look here: [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Objects/Creation/PoolingObjects/PoolingObjects.cxs|PoolingObjects.cxs]]. 

*Remove Objects*
If you need to remove objects, have a look at the [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Objects/Creation/RemoveObject/RemoveObject.cxs|RemoveObject.cxs]] script. 

>>> Data Storage
*Storing user defined data*
Sometime you need to store extra information inside an ftObject. For this, have a look at the [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Objects/DataStorage/DataStorage.cxs|DataStorage.cxs]] script. 

>>> Object hierachy
*Parent and childs*
If you need a parent child relationship of your objects, have a look at the [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Objects/Hierachy/ParentChild/ParentChild.cxs|ParentChild.cxs]] script. 

*Sort Objects*
If you need to sort objects in layers, have a look at the [[./data/fantomCX/examples/Objects/Hierachy/SortObjects/SortObjects.cxs|SortObjects.cxs]] script. 

